[[include component:image-block | name=Goblin | caption=Image dated circ. 1906]]

**Special Containment Procedures:** Translation of SCP-7535 is to be suspended, and MTF Phi-7 "Record Setters" dispatched to censor evidence of historical disruptions.[[footnote]]Tempus-class anomalies cause retroactive alteration to baseline reality.[[/footnote]]

**Description:** SCP-7535 is a book entitled "Tales of Gobliny" containing sixty-nine chapters written in an unknown language composed of Pig Latin and Goblish.[[footnote]]A form of broken English used by Goblins.[[/footnote]] 

Upon comprehension, SCP-7535 creates a temporal vulnerability localized to the reader, allowing up to one hundred //homo goblinensis// entities to manifest at random timeframes in the previous millennia. Entities will attack sapient lifeforms, steal items perceived to be valuable,[[footnote]]Including watches, jewelry, powdered wigs, and dentures.[[/footnote]] and escape via air balloon while directing guttural mating songs to nearby women.

**Addendum SCP-7535-1:** Following translation of SCP-7535 numerous //homo goblinensis// incursions were retroactively observed, requiring alteration of historical records for 1107, 1496, 1772, and 1906. Legends of goblin sightings are culturally normalized, and Foundation geneticists have been thus far successful in suppressing public awareness of "Hoblins".[[footnote]]Human-Goblin hybrids.[[/footnote]] 
